Bumps [regex](https://github.com/rust-lang/regex) from 1.3.1 to 1.3.4.
Changelog

Sourced from regex's changelog.

1.3.4 (2020-01-30)

This is a small bug fix release that fixes a bug related to the scoping of flags in a regex. Namely, before this fix, a regex like ((?i)a)b) would match aB despite the fact that b should not be matched case insensitively.

Bug fixes:

  • [BUG #640](rust-lang/regex#640): Fix bug related to the scoping of flags in a regex.

1.3.3 (2020-01-09)

This is a small maintenance release that upgrades the dependency on thread_local from 0.3 to 1.0. The minimum supported Rust version remains at Rust 1.28.

1.3.2 (2020-01-09)

This is a small maintenance release with some house cleaning and bug fixes.

New features:

  • [FEATURE #631](rust-lang/regex#631): Add a Match::range method an a From<Match> for Range impl.

Bug fixes:

  • [BUG #521](rust-lang/regex#521): Corrects /-/.splitn("a", 2) to return ["a"] instead of ["a", ""].
  • [BUG #594](rust-lang/regex#594): Improve error reporting when writing \p\.
  • [BUG #627](rust-lang/regex#627): Corrects /-/.split("a-") to return ["a", ""] instead of ["a"].
  • [BUG #633](rust-lang/regex#633): Squash deprecation warnings for the std::error::Error::description method.

  • 25d7c74 regex-syntax-0.6.14
  • 9b41e68 changelog: 1.3.4
  • ea4009a syntax: fix flag scoping issue
  • 2a8ddd0 1.3.3
  • f6f8276 deps: update to thread_local 1.0
  • ab5d913 1.3.2
  • 94a5886 syntax: release 0.6.13
  • 65d6bba api: fix for splitn("a", 2) returning extra ""
  • Additional commits viewable in compare view

Release notes *Sourced from [serde's releases](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/releases).* > ## v1.0.101 > - Report errors on malformed serde attributes, like `#[serde(rename =)]` -- the compiler used to reject these itself, but when the compiler relaxed its requirements on attribute syntax these malformed attributes began silently being ignored by serde_derive > > - Eliminate unused variable warning when using skip_serializing inside a tuple variant of an adjacently tagged enum ([#1617](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/serde-rs/serde/issues/1617), thanks [@​arilotter](https://github.com/arilotter)) > > - Support skip attribute inside of newtype variants ([#1622](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/serde-rs/serde/issues/1622), thanks [@​Xaeroxe](https://github.com/Xaeroxe)) > > ## v1.0.100 > - Provide `serde::ser::StdError` and `serde::de::StdError` which are either a re-export of `std::error::Error` (if Serde's "std" feature is enabled) or a new identical trait (otherwise). > > ```rust > #[cfg(feature = "std")] > pub use std::error::Error as StdError; > > #[cfg(not(feature = "std"))] > pub trait StdError: Debug + Display { > fn source(&self) -> Option<&(StdError + 'static)> { None } > } > ``` > > Serde's error traits `serde::ser::Error` and `serde::de::Error` require `std::error::Error` as a supertrait, but only when Serde is built with "std" enabled.
